Yuck (https://github.com/informarte/yuck) is provided under the terms
of the Mozilla Public License 2.0.

Some global constraint definitions (in the mzn/ folder) reuse
bits and pieces from the default definitions that come with the
MiniZinc 2.0.x distributions (https://github.com/MiniZinc/libminizinc)
which are used under the terms of the Mozilla Public License 2.0.

Yuck directly and transitively depends on some libraries, see the jar
files in the lib/ folder.

The following libraries are used under the terms of the revised BSD
license:

* The Scala Library
  (http://www.scala-lang.org)
* The Scala Standard Parser Combinators Library
  (https://github.com/scala/scala-parser-combinators)

The following libraries are used under the terms of the MIT license:

* The scopt library for parsing command line options
  (https://github.com/scopt/scopt)

The following libraries are used under the terms of the Eclipse
Public License 1.0:

* JGraphT
  (http://www.jgrapht.org)

The following libraries are used under the terms of the Apache
License 2.0:

* spray-json
  (https://github.com/spray/spray-json)

Please see the folder licenses/ for all copyright statements and the
licenses.
